description: Borrowed from Latin evictus, past participle of ēvincō (“to vanquish completely”). Doublet of evince.

verbs.description: evict (third-person singular simple present evicts, present participle evicting, simple past and past participle evicted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To expel (one or more people) from their property; to force (one or more people) to move out.
